after forking
go to your local branch

create another branch to solve bug or feature
git checkout -b "mybranch_from_myMain"

isme changes git add.. git commit.. git push karke changes mne apni branch ke remote mai push kar diye
(mylocalrepo--> main, mybranch_from_myMain)
code sirf mybranch_from_myMain me aega...

uske baad pull(merge request bna ke website ke help se hum changes directly open source ke "main" mai push kar dete hai)



ab hmaari feature branch to upto date hai... lekin hmmari main branch... opensource waale main ke saath sync mai nhi hai
(PR ke merge ke baad waise bhi feature branch delete ho jaati hai)

to open source repo ke main se apne git ke main ko kaise sync karen?????

git switch main 

(aapka local main hai)

usko theek karne ke uppae

git remote add upstream "remote repo ka path"    

upstream naam de rhe hai usko
jaise origin rakte hai .. kuch or bhi rakh sakte hai isse ek link bann jaega
isse jab hum git remote -v karenge to wo remote waali git repo ko bhi dikhaaane lgega

git fetch all
git merge upstream/main

or

git pull upstream main



git push 
or
git push origin main 
ye dono hi kaam karengi
ab ye mere remote ko update kar dega
